{
  "texts": [
    "Soldiers watched war-related 360° videos while their reactions were analyzed (e.g., Park et al. 2017).",
    "Interactive experiences were less common (30%), and their objective was to observe how individuals perform in various situations (e.g., Muñoz et al. 2020).",
    "In contrast, Explorative experiences were rarely used (10%).",
    "They were used to study the relationship between the way they move in a war scenario and their emotions (e.g., Malta et al. 2021).",
    "The objective was the same as for the Explorative with interaction experiences (20%) (e.g., Binsch et al. 2021)."
  ]
}